"```sql\nSELECT \n    COUNT(DISTINCT s.City) AS NumberOfCities,\n    s.City,\n    COUNT(sch.CDSCode) AS NumberOfSchools\nFROM \n    schools s\nJOIN \n    frpm f ON s.CDSCode = f.CDSCode\nWHERE \n    s.Magnet = 1\n    AND s.GSserved = 'K-8'\n    AND f.`NSLP Provision Status` = 'Multiple Provision Types'\nGROUP BY \n    s.City;\n```\n\nThis SQL query will count the number of cities that have schools offering a magnet program serving a grade span of Kindergarten to 8th grade and also count the number of such schools in each city that have a 'Multiple Provision Types' NSLP status."